    "narrative_summary": "Archer-Daniels-Midland Company reported first quarter 2026 financial results, with adjusted EPS of $0.71, up 1% from the prior year. The company raised its full-year 2026 adjusted EPS guidance to $4.15-$4.70 from $3.60-$4.25, citing improved performance in crushing and ethanol businesses due to U.S. biofuels policy clarity. The results included net negative mark-to-market and timing impacts of approximately $275 million, primarily in the Crushing subsegment."
